<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Abidjan Cabbage Salad</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>None</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Thinly sliced cabbage</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Shredded carrot</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Pineapple chunks</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Lemon; juice of</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Orange; juice of</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/3</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Vegetable oil</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Place cabbage, carrots &amp; pineapple into a large bowl. Mix the dressing by
  whisking all the ingredients together till creamy or by drizzling the oil
  into the juices while in a blender. Thoroughly blend the dressing &amp; the
  vegetables. Refrigerate or serve immediately.
  
  "Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant Cookbook"
